; Fixture: boundary nested shell modes
; Purpose: two concentric shells validating bitmask per-layer tracking and ordering.
;
; Shell layout (both centred at origin):
;   BoundaryShell_Outer  radius=4.0  CrossingPolicy=EntryAndExit(2)  BiasDirection=Up    BiasStrength=0.12
;   BoundaryShell_Inner  radius=2.0  CrossingPolicy=EntryOnly(0)      BiasDirection=Right BiasStrength=0.12
;
; Snap index order follows scene tree order:
;   BoundaryShell_Outer  → snap index 0 (bit 0 in blvInsideMask)
;   BoundaryShell_Inner  → snap index 1 (bit 1 in blvInsideMask)
;
; Crossing sequence for a ray travelling straight through both shells (-Z direction):
;   Step A: enters outer (r crosses 4.0 → inside outer, outside inner)
;           entryBits bit 0 set → dispatch: Up bias on outer (EntryAndExit)
;           Log: "[BLV] entry event: layer=0 name='BoundaryShell_Outer'"
;   Step B: enters inner (r crosses 2.0 → inside both)
;           entryBits bit 1 set → dispatch: Right bias on inner (EntryOnly)
;           Log: "[BLV] entry event: layer=1 name='BoundaryShell_Inner'"
;   Step C: exits inner (r crosses 2.0 → inside outer only)
;           exitBits bit 1 set → inner is EntryOnly → NO dispatch
;   Step D: exits outer (r crosses 4.0 → outside both)
;           exitBits bit 0 set → dispatch: Up bias on outer (EntryAndExit)
;           Log: "[BLV] exit event: layer=0 name='BoundaryShell_Outer'"
;
; Expected visual for on-axis ray:
;   Two upward nudges (entry + exit outer) and one rightward nudge (entry inner).
;   Net displacement on backdrop: ≈up+right composite. Central dot appears shifted
;   down-left in the film (rays aimed toward it now land above-right of it).
;
; Layer ordering check: bit 0 (outer) and bit 1 (inner) are both set for steps between r=2 and r=4.
;   Both bits update correctly in a single step: ComputeInsideMask computes both atomically.
;
; Start-inside check: camera at Z=8, outer radius=4. Camera is outside both shells. ✓
; Grazing note: rays that clip only the outer shell (2 < r < 4 at closest approach) trigger
;   outer crossing events without inner events. This is correct and expected.

